<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-14831] Illegal state errors should be fatal in transactional producer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14831</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-14830&quot; title=&quot;Illegal state error in transactional producer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-14830&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-14830&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the producer hit an illegal state error. The error was propagated to the &lt;tt&gt;Sender&lt;/tt&gt; thread and logged, but the producer otherwise continued on. It would be better to make illegal state errors fatal since continuing to write to transactions when the internal state is inconsistent may cause incorrect and unpredictable behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13529502">KAFKA-14831</key>
            <summary>Illegal state errors should be fatal in transactional producer</summary>
